<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="General_description">General description</span></h2>
<p>The Cessna (172) Skyhawk G1000 panel consists of two layouts, for a left and right (touch) monitor. This represents the pilot and co-pilot/passenger side of the glareshield.
The Cessna Skyhawk has been around for more than 65 years, but is still one of the number one selling aircraft. In the 2000's the Skyhawk could be fitted with a G1000 avionics suite, and this is nowadays the only variant available. This panel makes for a perfect training tool, for real life pilots who want to get familiar with the Cessna Skyhawk and the G1000 avionics. Why burn expensive hours in the real aircraft, if you can make yourself familiar for just a fraction of the cost. But of course this panel is also perfect for those who want to do some casual flying in a great all-round aircraft.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="X-Plane_12">X-Plane 12</span></h2>
<p>In X-Plane 12 you can make use of the streaming functionality. Meaning that you do not have to set up the pop-outs. If you do want to use pop-outs, then make sure that you turn off the streaming functionality of both G1000's. This can be done in the user properties of the instrument.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Microsoft_Flight_Simulator">Microsoft Flight Simulator</span></h2>
<div style="background: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.1); border: solid thin grey; padding: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center;&#125;&#125;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Warning.png" class="image" title="Info"><img alt="Info" src="/images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/18px-Warning.png" decoding="async" width="18" height="18" srcset="/images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/27px-Warning.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/36px-Warning.png 2x" /></a> <span style="margin-top:-0px; padding-left:16px; display:block;">MSFS requires you to use pop-outs for this panel. These only work on the same computer as the flight simulator!</span></div>
<p>For MSFS you will have to use pop-outs for the G1000 screens. On our <a href="/index.php?title=Pop_outs" title="Pop outs">pop outs</a> wiki guide, you can find instructions on how to set this up.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Instruments">Instruments</span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Altimeter">Altimeter</span></h3>
<p>In X-Plane the standby altimeter works separately from the G1000 altitude. In MSFS unfortunately, the standby altimeter is always linked to the G1000 altimeter, this is a limitation of the flight simulator.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="ELT">ELT</span></h3>
<p>Set the switch to ON for one second, and then back to ARM to test the ELT.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Panel_switcher">Panel switcher</span></h3>
<p>In the starter-key / flaps panel, you will find 3 buttons with icons.
</p>
<ul><li>Key: Brings up the panel with the starter-key and flaps handle.</li>
<li>Fuel: Brings up the fuel panel. This contains the fuel selector and fuel cut-off.</li>
<li>Electric: Brings up the circuit breaker panel. Note that the fuse panel does not work at the moment. Circuit breaker panel implementation for MSFS 2024 is still a to-do.</li></ul>
